[b]TVO - The Agenda with Steve Paikin, February 23 2011: Rise of the Global Elite[/b]

[u]The Debate: Rise of the Global Elite[/u] 

The already wealthy have emerged from the global recession in an even wealthier position. What does the rise of global elites mean to power and influence at home and abroad? 

[u]Guests:[/u]

[b]Chrystia Freeland[/b] is the global editor at large for Reuters. She also blogs for Reuters.

[b]Shamus Khan[/b] is a professor in the Department of Psychology at Columbia University. Read more about Shamus Khan.

[b]Partha Mohanram[/b] is a professor at the Rotman School of Management, University of Toronto.

[b]Armine Yalnizyan[/b] is with the Canadian Centre for Policy Alternatives (CCPA). A number of her publications can be viewed at the CCPA website.

